susy.quest.db.284.desc=§6Element§r: Strontium (Sr)%n§bAtomic Number§r: 38%n§aAtomic Mass§r: 87.62 amu%n§cMelting Point§r: 1050 K%n§5Boiling Point§r: 1655 K%n§6Properties§r: Strontium is an alkaline earth metal used in pyrotechnics to produce red-colored flames. It is also used in the production of cathode ray tubes and in certain medical applications.%n
