susy.quest.db.309.title=076 | 锇
susy.quest.db.309.desc=§6Element§r: Osmium (Os)%n§bAtomic Number§r: 76%n§aAtomic Mass§r: 190.23 amu%n§cMelting Point§r: 3306 K%n§5Boiling Point§r: 5285 K%n§6Properties§r: Osmium is a transition metal known for its high density and extreme hardness. It is used in certain alloys, in the production of fountain pen tips, and in some electrical contacts.%n
